#: ../../simulator.rst:125
msgid "glaciers flow downslope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../simulator.rst:126
msgid ""
"the steeper the slope the thinner the glacier (larger along-slope "
"gravitational force)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../simulator.rst:127
msgid ""
"the flatter the slope the larger the equilibrium velocity. When the "
"glacier is thin (has not much mass) the along-slope component is more "
"important. When the glacier is getting thicker the perpendicular "
"component is getting more weight. This partly explains slower velocities "
"for flatter slopes at the start of the model run, and higher velocities "
"when the glacier is getting thicker. For steeper slopes the velocities at"
" the start are large and so more ice is transported downwards, and the "
"glacier stays relatively thin."
msgstr ""

